pathie-cpp
------------------------------------------
This is the Pathie project. It aims to provide a C++ library that covers all
needs of pathname manipulation and filename fiddling, without having to worry
about the underlying platform. That is, it is a glue library that allows you to
create platform-independent filename handling code with special regard to
Unicode path names.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.1-1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libiconv2-1.14-3
  libpathie-devel-0.1.0-1bl1
  libpathie0-0.1.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.32.0-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Quintus/pathie-cpp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Quintus/pathie-cpp/archive/v0.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack pathie-cpp-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./pathie-cpp-0.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pathie-cpp-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/pathie-cpp-0.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpathie0-0.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpathie-devel-0.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(pathie-cpp)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/pathie-cpp.README
  /usr/share/doc/pathie-cpp/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/pathie-cpp/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/pathie-cpp/README.md

(libpathie0)
  /usr/bin/cygpathie-0.dll

(libpathie-devel)
  /usr/include/pathie/entry_iterator.hpp
  /usr/include/pathie/errors.hpp
  /usr/include/pathie/path.hpp
  /usr/include/pathie/pathie.hpp
  /usr/include/pathie/temp.hpp
  /usr/lib/libpathie.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/pathie-cpp.pc

